This script sorts an array of integers using the Bubble Sort algorithm. Here's how it works:

1. The outer loop (`for i in range(n-1)`) iterates `n-1` times, where `n` is the length of the array.
2. The inner loop (`for j in range(0, n-i-1)`) compares each pair of adjacent elements and swaps them if they're in the wrong order.
3. After the inner loop completes for all pairs, the largest element has "bubbled" to the end of the array, so we start checking from the last `n-i-1` positions (i.e., 0-indexed).
4. We repeat steps 2 and 3 until no more swaps are needed, indicating that the array is sorted.

